                type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>For the views of the Policy Planning Staff on the Mediterranean area, with
                    particular reference to Greece and Italy, see Section IV of <gloss
                        target="#t_PPS1">PPS</gloss> 23, February 24, 1948, volume I. The conclusion
                    reached in this paper was “that our policy with respect to Greece and Italy, and
                    the Mediterranean area in general, should be based upon the objective of
                    demonstration to the Russians that: <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>the reduction of the communist threat will lead to our military
                            withdrawal from the area; but that</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>further communist pressure will only have the effect of involving us
                            more deeply in a military sense.”</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
